---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <section id="intro">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>ML Engineer building intelligent systems at scale</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Principal ML Engineer | Music Cognition Research</p>
      <p class="lead">
        Twenty years at Walmart designing multi-echelon MILP systems across 23 fulfillment
        centers, with documented supply chain impact measured in hundreds of millions of
        dollars. Currently building production ML at Acorns: winback modeling on Databricks
        with MLflow and SHAP.
      </p>
      <p class="lead">
        Exploring where machine learning meets music understanding and human emotion.
        Potential PhD direction: music cognition and optimization as an interdisciplinary
        research path.
      </p>
      <p class="scroll-hint">
        <a href="#work">Explore my work below &darr;</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="work">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Work</h2>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Designed Multi-Echelon MILP System for Supply Chain Network</h3>
        <p class="meta">Walmart &middot; 2006&ndash;May 2025</p>
        <p>
          Designed the formulation and directed engineering implementation for supply chain
          optimization at scale: not project management alone, but MILP systems thinking
          deployed across real infrastructure.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>23 fulfillment centers, multi-layer network design</li>
          <li>CPLEX formulations: simplex, branch-and-bound, cutting planes, Dantzig-Wolfe</li>
          <li>Inventory optimization via pull-forward and capacity-capping systems</li>
          <li>Order Well: Kafka-based async order optimization, 95% good-pick utilization</li>
          <li>13B daily transactions, 24 direct reports</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="metrics">
          <span>$900M documented savings</span>
          <span>23 FCs</span>
          <span>13B daily transactions</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Built Production LightGBM Churn/Winback Model</h3>
        <p class="meta">Acorns &middot; Current contractor engagement (~6 months)</p>
        <p>
          End-to-end ML lifecycle on an imbalanced production dataset: feature engineering,
          hyperparameter tuning, threshold optimization, and explainability for deployment.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>~1% positive rate, 126K rows; scale_pos_weight ~77</li>
          <li>LightGBM with Optuna Bayesian hyperparameter tuning</li>
          <li>Threshold optimization via net revenue sweep</li>
          <li>Deployment stack: Databricks, MLflow, SHAP</li>
          <li>Production code: PySpark, condensed single-call style</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="metrics">
          <span>Recall: 0.881</span>
          <span>ROC-AUC: 0.924</span>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="projects">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Projects</h2>

      <article class="card">
        <p class="tag">Primary</p>
        <h3>Music Intelligence Pipeline</h3>
        <p>
          Emotion-aware music analysis system that predicts arousal and valence from audio,
          then tags music semantically to prevent hallucination and provide an interpretable
          interface over raw predictions.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Dataset: DEAM (Database for Emotional Analysis in Music)</li>
          <li>Features: librosa, OpenSMILE</li>
          <li>Model: XGBoost for arousal/valence prediction</li>
          <li>Interface: Shiny for Python (interactive querying)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Raw predictions (R&sup2; ~0.43) are directional, not precise. The semantic layer
          interprets them into broad emotional tags: uplifting, introspective, and similar.
          All models are approximations; usefulness beats precision in human-centered domains.
        </p>
        <div class="metrics">
          <span>R&sup2; ~0.43</span>
          <span>Pearson r ~0.66</span>
        </div>
        <div class="links">
          <a href="https://github.com/JeffGoseland/music_intelligence_pipeline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <p class="tag">Secondary</p>
        <h3>Neural Bard: Spotify LLM Playlist Generator</h3>
        <p>
          Full-stack application that generates Spotify playlists from natural language via
          LLM (Grok), then creates them through OAuth. Applied music plus LLM: shipped product,
          not just research.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Frontend: HTML5, Bootstrap 5, vanilla JavaScript</li>
          <li>Backend: Netlify serverless functions</li>
          <li>LLM: x.ai Grok-3-fast</li>
          <li>Features: duplicate detection, smart playlist management, OAuth flow</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="links">
          <a href="https://spotify-llm-driven-playlist.netlify.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Live demo</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/JeffGoseland/spotify-llm-driven-playlist" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <p class="tag">Tertiary</p>
        <h3>Aimpoint Digital LP Challenge</h3>
        <p>
          Mixed-integer linear programming applied to a vehicle routing dataset using
          scipy.optimize.linprog with the HiGHS solver. Demonstrates MILP fluency in code:
          constraint design, solver selection, and practical optimization workflow.
        </p>
        <div class="links">
          <a href="https://github.com/JeffGoseland/ad-challenge" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="about">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>About</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Principal-level ML engineer with two decades of production systems experience at
        Walmart, now focused on rigorous ML engineering and music cognition research.
      </p>
      <p>
        MS Data Science, University of Notre Dame (May 2026). Currently engaged with Acorns
        on production winback modeling. Also building
        <a href="https://noeticiq.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NoeticIQ</a>,
        a consulting brand at the intersection of data and cognition.
      </p>
      <p><strong>Research interests</strong></p>
      <ul style="margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 1.25rem;">
        <li>Music cognition: emotional trajectory, arousal/valence, Tonnetz geometry</li>
        <li>Optimization: MILP, integer programming, constraint design</li>
        <li>Human-centered AI systems with interpretable interfaces</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Exploring PhD paths in music cognition plus optimization: ML/CS with a music focus,
        or music informatics with an optimization angle. Preference for local/part-time,
        remote funded international, or selective full-time programs.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top: 1rem;">
        <em>All models are approximations. Usefulness beats precision. Interpretability matters in human-centered domains.</em>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="contact">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <div class="links">
        <a href="mailto:jeff@goseland.org">jeff@goseland.org</a>
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jeffgoseland/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/JeffGoseland" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
        <a href="https://noeticiq.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NoeticIQ</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
